    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[BEFS89] Burr, S. A. and Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Faudree, R. J. and Schelp, R.\nH., On the difference between consecutive {R}amsey numbers. Utilitas Math. (1989), 115--118.",
      "remarks": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{o}s, who could not even prove whether $R(k+1,k)-R(k,k)>k^c$ for any $c>1$.\n\nIt is trivial that $R(k+1,k)-R(k,k)\\geq k-2$. Burr, Erd\\H{o}s, Faudree, and Schelp \\cite{BEFS89} proved\\[R(k+1,k)-R(k,k)\\geq 2k-5.\\]See also [544] for a similar question concerning $R(3,k)$, and [1014] for the general off-diagonal case."
    },
