    "intended": "Let $R(k,l)$ be the usual Ramsey number: the smallest $n$ such that if the edges of $K_n$ are coloured red and blue then there exists either a red $K_k$ or a blue $K_l$.\n\nProve the existence of some $c>0$ such that\\[\\lim_{k\\to \\infty}\\frac{R(k+1,k)}{R(k,k)}> 1+c.\\]",
